Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ColorClassifier
    The ColorClassifier class samples the color sensor in RGB mode and uses the color data to classify an objects color as one of the known enumerated values.
    Display
    This class is used to display the content of the odometer variables (x, y, theta).
    LightLocalization
    LightLocalization leverages the readings of both left and right light sensors to snap to perpendicular gridlines.
    Main
    The main driver class for the lab.
    Map
    This class is used to create the map used by the Navigation class.
    Navigation  
    ObjectDetection
    Object Detection class polls the ultrasonic sensor to detect nearby objects and executes the necessary logic to circumvent avoid walls or attach to the stranded vehicle.
    Odometer
    The odometer class keeps track of the robot's (x, y, theta) position.
    Resources
    This class is used to define static resources in one place for easy access and to avoid cluttering the rest of the codebase.
    UltrasonicLocalizer
    The UltrasonicLocalizer implements two different types of localization methods which use an ultrasonic sensor.The two types of localizations include falling edge (when robot starts by facing away from the wall) and rising edge (when robot starts by facing the wall).
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ColorClassifier.RingColor
    Enumerated color values.
